## üß† YOU HAVE MEMORY ‚Äî USE IT BEFORE CODING!

This project has a **shared knowledge base** (meh) with facts from previous AI sessions.
It has bugs, architecture decisions, changelogs, TODOs ‚Äî things you can't learn from code alone.

### MANDATORY first steps (every session):

```
mcp_meh_meh_context({"action": "show"})                                       # 1. Verify connection (should be "{KB_NAME}")
mcp_meh_meh_notify({"action": "get"})                                         # 2. Check what changed since last session
mcp_meh_meh_facts({"action": "browse", "path": "@", "mode": "tree"})          # 3. See knowledge structure
```

If KB is not `{KB_NAME}`:
```
mcp_meh_meh_context({"action": "switch_kb", "kb_name": "{KB_NAME}"})
```

### BEFORE touching any code area:

```
mcp_meh_meh_facts({"action": "search", "query": "area you're about to work on"})
```

This prevents you from repeating fixed bugs, violating architecture decisions, or duplicating work.

### AFTER modifying code:

```
mcp_meh_meh_write({"action": "add", "path": "@changelog/short-name", "content": "# What Changed\n\n..."})
mcp_meh_meh_notify({"action": "ack", "notification_ids": ["*"]})
```

**If you don't document, the next AI session starts from zero.**

